<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06251090 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06251090 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  US; CALIFORNIA; EMPLOYMENT; STATISTIC  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  The U.S. unemployment rate failed to budge from 6.8 percent in August, thegovernment reported Friday.;   The nation's economy did begin creating morejobs again last month, but the increase was modest. The Labor Departmentreport showed that payrolls grew by 34,000 in August after a 43,000-jobdecline the previous month. At the same time, a large number of discouragedjob-seekers stopped looking for work altogether.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  JOBLESS RATE STAYS AT 6.8%; STATE RATE FALLS  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Signs of widespread weakness in the Labor Department report indicate theU.S. economy is in danger of sputtering back into recession, several privateeconomists said.;   California's jobless rate dropped to 7.3 percent in Augustfrom 7.6 percent in July. The rate was 8.2 percent in June and 5.5 percent inAugust 1990. It was the lowest rate for the state since December 1990, when itstood at 6.8 percent.;   The Mortgage Bankers Association said Friday thepercentage of Americans who are behind on their mortgage payments hit thehighest level in nearly five years during the April-June quarter.;   Theassociation said its survey showed that the proportion of homeowners 30 daysor more late on their payments climbed to a seasonally adjusted 5.28 percentin the second quarter from 4.95 percent in the first quarter and 4.52 percenta year earlier. It was the highest since 5.32 percent of mortgages weredelinquent in the fourth quarter of 1986.;   The Commerce Department's Bureauof Economic Analysis reported Friday that per capita income rose 5.4 percentin 1990 to $18,691, down from 6.8 percent growth in 1989.;   The RockyMountain region -- up 6.6 percent to $16,668 -- and Southwest -- up 6.2percent to $16,311 -- posted the fastest increases. Income grew 4.9 percent to$20,130 in the Far West.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Washington  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910907  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  September  </MONTH><PG.COL>  10E  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  284  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday, September 7, 199100251090,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>